Gets CFB recruiting information for a single year with filters available for team, recruit type, state and position.

Source: R/geocode_cities.R
geocode_cities.Rd

If you would like to get cfb recruiting information based on position groups during a time period for all FBS teams, please see cfb_position_recruiting function.

geocode_cities(
  year,
  team = NULL,
  recruit_type = NULL,
  state = NULL,
  position = NULL
)

Arguments

year

Year (Integer, 4 digits YYYY, required)
team

Team information (String optional)
recruit_type

default API return is 'HighSchool', other options include 'JUCO' or 'PrepSchool' (String optional) - For position group information
state

Two letter State abbreviation (String optional)
position

Position Group (String optional) - options include:

  • Offense: 'PRO', 'DUAL', 'RB', 'FB', 'TE', 'OT', 'OG', 'OC', 'WR'

  • Defense: 'CB', 'S', 'OLB', 'ILB', 'WDE', 'SDE', 'DT'

  • Special Teams: 'K', 'P'

Examples
